lead_paragraph: Cyprus' president has warned U.N. Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon that time is needed to negotiate a deal reunifying the ethnically-split island without "deficiencies, gaps and ambiguities" that may lead Greek and Turkish Cypriots to reject it in referendums.

headline.main: Cyprus President Warns UN Chief No Rush to Reach Peace Deal
headline.print_headline: Cyprus President Warns UN Chief No Rush to Reach Peace Deal
